Code for the NAACL'21 paper On the Embeddings of Variables in Recurrent Neural Networks for Source Code

The official PyTorch implementation of:
* __On the Embeddings of Variables in Recurrent Neural Networks for Source Code__ [[arxiv](https://arxiv.org/abs/2010.12693)] (accepted to [NAACL'21](https://2021.naacl.org/))
result.original_header: RNNs with Dynamic Embeddings for Source Code Processing

RNNs with Dynamic Embeddings for Source Code Processing

result.value: The experiments were conducted on the [Python150k](https://www.sri.inf.ethz.ch/py150) and [JavaScript150k](https://www.sri.inf.ethz.ch/js150) datasets, resplitted according to https://github.com/bayesgroup/code_transformers. Please follow [this instruction](https://github.com/bayesgroup/code_transformers/tree/main/data_utils) to obtain data.

Parts of this code are based on the following repositories:
* [A Transformer-based Approach for Source Code Summarization](https://github.com/wasiahmad/NeuralCodeSum) 
* [OpenNMT](https://github.com/OpenNMT/OpenNMT-py)
* [DrQA](https://github.com/facebookresearch/DrQA)
* https://github.com/oleges1/code-completion
